  "prompt": "What are the nutritional differences between lemons and limes?",
  "response": "Lemons and limes are both citrus fruits and share many nutritional similarities, but there are some differences in their nutrient profiles. Here's a comparison:\n\n### Calories:\n- **Lemon**: Approximately 24 calories per 100 grams.\n- **Lime**: Approximately 30 calories per 100 grams.\n\n### Macronutrients:\n- **Carbohydrates**: \n  - Lemon: About 9 grams per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: About 11 grams per 100 grams.\n- **Sugars**:\n  - Lemon: Approximately 2.5 grams per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: Approximately 1.7 grams per 100 grams.\n- **Fiber**:\n  - Lemon: Around 2.8 grams per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: Around 2.8 grams per 100 grams.\n- **Fat**: Negligible amounts in both fruits.\n- **Protein**:\n  - Lemon: Around 1.1 grams per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: Around 0.7 grams per 100 grams.\n\n### Vitamins:\n- **Vitamin C**:\n  - Lemon: About 53 mg per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: About 29 mg per 100 grams.\n- **Vitamin A**: Both lemons and limes contain small amounts.\n- **Folate (Vitamin B9)**:\n  - Lemon: About 11 micrograms per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: About 8 micrograms per 100 grams.\n\n### Minerals:\n- **Potassium**:\n  - Lemon: Approximately 138 mg per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: Approximately 102 mg per 100 grams.\n- **Calcium**:\n  - Lemon: About 26 mg per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: About 33 mg per 100 grams.\n- **Magnesium**:\n  - Lemon: Around 8 mg per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: About 6 mg per 100 grams.\n\n### Other Nutrients:\n- **Phosphorus**: \n  - Lemon: Around 16 mg per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: Around 18 mg per 100 grams.\n- **Iron**:\n  - Lemon: About 0.6 mg per 100 grams.\n  - Lime: About 0.2 mg per 100 grams.\n\nDespite these differences, both lemons and limes offer a range of nutrients and can be valuable additions to a healthy diet. Their high vitamin C content and antioxidant properties are particularly noteworthy. Additionally, both fruits contain flavonoids that can contribute to various health benefits, including anti-inflammatory and immune-boosting effects.",
